Were you able to solve the issue? My team ran into the same problem, you need to make a new swerve configuration you can do the following:

import com.swervedrivespecialties.swervelib.Mk4ModuleConfiguration;

create a instance: public Mk4ModuleConfiguration SwerveConfig; set the values: SwerveConfig.setSteerCurrentLimit(SteerLimit); SwerveConfig.setDriveCurrentLimit(DriveLimit);

Set the modules to use that configuration: (my team is using Neos)

m_frontLeftModule = Mk4iSwerveModuleHelper.createNeo( SwerveConfig, Mk4iSwerveModuleHelper.GearRatio.L1, FRONT_LEFT_MODULE_DRIVE_MOTOR, FRONT_LEFT_MODULE_STEER_MOTOR, FRONT_LEFT_MODULE_STEER_ENCODER, FRONT_LEFT_MODULE_STEER_OFFSET
